<kml>

<concept name=Restrain>
<superconcept name=Obstruct>

<hr>
<h3>Component Semantics:</h3>
<component tag=Restrain>
  <definition>prevent an object from moving</definition>
  <requiredslot name=object>
    <restriction>a Tangible-Entity</restriction>
  </requiredslot>
  <requiredslot name=post-conditions>
    <restriction><slot>object</slot> is the <slot>object</slot> of a
      <conceptref name=Be-Restrained></restriction>
  </requiredslot>
  <primaryslot name=agent>
    <inheritedfrom name=Obstruct>
    <restriction>causes <slot>object</slot> to be Restrained</restriction>
  </primaryslot>
  <wnsynsets><verb>restrain#1, restrain#3
  </verb></wnsynsets>
  <wnsynsets><verb>confine#6, hold#4, hold_back#2, keep#14, keep_back#1
  </verb></wnsynsets>
</component>

<musing>
Restraining an <slot>object</slot> prevents all movement of the 
<slot>object</slot>. In order to <conceptref name=Move> a Restrained
<slot>object</slot> it must be taken out of the <conceptref name=Be-Restrained>
state with a <conceptref name=Unrestrain> action.
</musing>
